# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# Tutorial 11 -- interactive visualization sandbox for the dislocation-core
# figure.
#
# Loads the relaxed screw-dislocation cylinder written by screw.lmp and
# renders the view along the dislocation line: the two Shockley partial
# cores and the stacking-fault ribbon between them.  pair_style zero only
# provides the neighbor list that the common neighbor analysis needs.
#   1. Run screw.lmp first (writes screw.data), or fetch it from the
#      solution folder.
#   2. Open this file in LAMMPS-GUI and run it; use the Image Viewer to
#      rotate/zoom, or edit the write_dump line and re-run.
variable ghost index 0.5       # opacity of the fcc bulk atoms

units metal
dimension 3
boundary s s p
atom_style atomic

read_data screw.data

pair_style zero 4.0
pair_coeff * *

compute cna all cna/atom 3.45
region chunk cylinder z 0.0 0.0 25 -1.0 10.0
group chunk region chunk

run 0 post no
write_dump chunk image screw-core.png c_cna type &
   size 1000 1000 zoom 5.0 shiny 0.2  fsaa yes &
   view 65 80 ssao yes 453983 0.6 box no 0.0 &
   center s 0.5 0.5 0.6 &
   modify backcolor white adiam 1 3.2 &
   color map1 0.267 0.005 0.329 color map2 0.191 0.407 0.556 &
   color map3 0.208 0.719 0.473 color map4 0.993 0.906 0.144 &
   amap 0 5 cf 0.0 4 min map1 0.333 map2 0.667 map3 max map4
